broaden /ˈbrɔːdən/

(broadening,broadened,broadens) 

1. V-I When something broadens , it becomes wider. 变宽 

例： The trails broadened into roads. 小径变宽成大路了。 

2. V-T/V-I When you broaden something such as your experience or popularity, or when it broadens , the number of things or people that it includes becomes greater. 扩宽; 开阔 

例： We must broaden our appeal. 我们必须扩大我们的吸引力。 

例： I thought you wanted to broaden your horizons. 我以为你想拓宽自己的视野。

